r=Sarasaviya | accessdate=15 August 2019}}</ref>\n* ''Pulina Prasada'' <ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/031221/tv/18.htm | title=\u2018Sand Castle\u2019: Yet another love story | publisher=Sunday Times | accessdate=16 August 2019}}</ref>\n* ''Ran Hiru Res''\n* ''Rasthiyadukaraya''\n* ''Rathriya Manaram''\n* ''Sahodaraya''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2017/11/16/?fn=sa1711166 |title=Sahodaraya on saturday|publisher=Sarasaviya |accessdate=17 November 2017}}</ref>\n* ''Samanalayano''<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/030323/tv/3.html#3 | title='Samanalayano': A tale of love | publisher=Sunday Times | accessdate=16 August 2019}}</ref>\n* ''Samanalunta Wedithiyanna'' <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/071111/TV/tv-times000012.html |title=\u2018Samanalunta Wedithiyanna\u2019 |publisher=Sunday Times |accessdate=11 December 2019}}</ref>\n* ''Sanda Ginigath Rathriya'' <ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/020804/tv/1.html#1 | title=New film on mini screen | publisher=Sunday Times| accessdate=29 November 2019}}</ref>\n* ''Sinansenna Anuththara'' <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/071111/TV/tv-times000011.html |title=\u2018Sinansenna Anuththara\u2019 : A tale of two couples |publisher=Sunday Times |accessdate=11 December 2019}}</ref>\n* ''Thaara''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timeout.com/sri-lanka/theatre/tele-dramas-on-tv |title=Thara on Sarnavahini |publisher=Timeout |accessdate=12 July 2018}}</ref>\n* ''Thunmanthanna''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pressreader.com/sri-lanka/daily-mirror-sri-lanka/20120521/283124245929227 |title=Thummanthanna on Sarnavahini |publisher=Timeout |accessdate=12 July 2018}}</ref>\n* ''Uthuwan Kande Sura Saradiyal''<ref>{{cite news|title=Sudath brings Saradial back |url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/060917/TV/tv1.html |work=Sunday Times}}</ref>\n* ''Vishmaya'' \n* ''Warna''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://archives.dailynews.lk/2005/06/25/fea06.htm |title=Warna: An analysis of the social spectrum |publisher=Daily News |accessdate=12 July 2018}}</ref>\n* ''Wasuli Kanda''<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/140202/magazine/wasuli-kanda-every-saturday-81371.html | title=\u2018Wasuli Kanda\u2019 every Saturday | publisher=Sunday Times | accessdate=20 November 2019}}</ref>\n* ''Weeraya Gedara Awith''<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.pressreader.com/sri-lanka/daily-mirror-sri-lanka/20190114/282815012404161 | title=Weeraya Gedara Ewith on Rupavahini | publisher=Daily Mirror| accessdate=30 July 2019}}</ref>\n{{Div col end}}\n\n==Filmography==\nRavindra's first major role in a film came through 2004 film ''[[Aadaraneeya Wassaanaya]]'' as Kasun directed by [[Senesh Dissanaike Bandara]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://films.lk/sinhala-cinema-artist-roshan-ravindra--284.html | title=Roshan Ravindra - \u0dbb\u0ddc\u0dc2\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dca \u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb | publisher=Sinhala Cinema Database| accessdate=30 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=First Sri Lankan star to enter \u2018Global Glamour Olympics\u2019 {{!}} The Sunday Times Sri Lanka|url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/160717/magazine/first-sri-lankan-star-to-enter-global-glamour-olympics-201014.html|work=www.sundaytimes.lk}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Film !! Role !! Ref.\n|-\n| 2004 || ''[[Aadaraneeya Wassaanaya]]'' || Kasun || <ref>{{cite web | url=http://archives.dailynews.lk/2004/06/16/artscop01.html | title=Love in the first flush of youth | publisher=Daily News| accessdate=30 July 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[Uppalawanna]]'' || Rebel || <ref>{{cite news|title=\u2018Uppalawanna\u2019 in a record run|url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/070826/TV/tv_2.html|work=www.sundaytimes.lk}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2008 || ''[[Heart FM (film)|Heart FM]]'' || Cameo role || \n|-\n| 2009 || ''[[Ekamath Eka Rateka]]'' ||  || <ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/090531/Magazine/sundaytimestvtimes_07.html | title=Sanath ventures to filmmaking wit