oman at the dinner table says she drinks because it makes sex better, Karen reaches over and fills her glass with wine; and when she becomes upset and leaves, Karen says \"Oh, yeah. Just where I was hoping this evening was going.\", grabs her purse and follows after her.) <br /> Vince is Will's partner. <br> {{Citation needed|reason=Per WP:VERIFY \u2013 Verify sexual orientation of all characters.|date=June 2018}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| 1999 || ''[[Oh, Grow Up]]'' || [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] || Ford Lowell <br /> Sal || [[John Ducey]] <br /> [[Ed Marinaro]] || Ford is a married man who left his wife after realizing he was gay.<ref name=Walters2001>{{cite book|last1=Walters|first1=Suzanna Danuta|title=All the Rage: The Story of Gay Visibility in America|date=2001|edition=1st|chapter=5. All Gay, All the Time?|page=[https://archive.org/details/allragestoryofga00walt/page/95 95]|publisher=[[University of Chicago Press]]|isbn=0-226-87231-9|url=https://archive.org/details/allragestoryofga00walt/page/95}} ([https://books.google.com/books?id=2pSH73isp94C&dq=isbn%3A0226872319&q=all+gay%2C+all+the+time#v=snippet&q=all%20gay%2C%20all%20the%20time&f=false Snippet]) (p. 100)</ref> Sal is lead character Hunter's ([[Stephen Dunham]]) boss.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Tropiano|first1=Stephen|title=The Prime Time Closet: A History of Gays and Lesbians on TV|date=2002|publisher=[[Applause Theatre & Cinema Books]]|isbn=978-1557835574 |url=https://archive.org/details/primetimecloseta00trop}} (p. 292)</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| 1999\u20132000 || ''[[Strangers with Candy]]'' || [[Comedy Central]] || Jerri Blank <br /> Geoffrey Jellineck <br /> Chuck Noblet || [[Amy Sedaris]] <br />[[Paul Dinello]] <br /> [[Stephen Colbert]] || Jerri is bisexual. Jellineck and Noblet carried on a clandestine affair. {{Citation needed|reason=Per WP:VERIFY \u2013 Verify sexual orientation of all characters.|date=June 2018}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| 1999\u20132001 || ''[[Beggars and Choosers (TV series)|