berg|first1=Lesley|last2=Rose|first2=Lacey|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/two-a-men-amber-tamblyn-600422|title='Two and a Half Men': Amber Tamblyn to Play Charlie's Daughter|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=August 7, 2013}}</ref> <br /> Whilst Alan is portrayed as a heterosexual man, he sometimes likes to crossdress in Evelyn's clothes and has made moves towards [[Walden Schmidt]] that suggest same-sex attraction. {{Citation needed|reason=Per WP:VERIFY \u2013 Verify sexual orientation of all characters.|date=July 2019}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| 2003\u20132009 || ''[[Reno 911!]]'' || [[Comedy Central]] || Lieutenant Dangle <br /> Deputy Kimball || [[Thomas Lennon (actor)|Thomas Lennon]] <br /> [[Mary Birdsong]] || {{Citation needed|reason=Per WP:VERIFY \u2013 Verify sexual orientation of all characters.|date=June 2018}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| 2003\u20132006 || ''[[Aqu\u00ed no hay quien viva]]'' || [[Antena 3 (Spain)|Antena 3]] || Mauri Hidalgo <br /> Fernando Navarro <br /> Bea Villarejo <br /> Diego \u00c1lvarez <br /> Rosa Izquierdo<br />Ana<br />Abel|| [[Luis Merlo]] <br /> [[Adri\u00e0 Collado]] <br /> [[Eva Isanta]] <br /> [[Mariano Alameda]] <br /> [[Mar\u00eda Almud\u00e9ver]]<br />[[Vanesa Romero]]<br />[[Alberto Maneiro]]|| Stable gay relationship between main characters Mauri and Fernando. During a time they were broken up, Mauri had a relationship with Diego, who left him for another man and later regretted it. But by then Mauri and Fernando were together again. <br> Mauri also has a son by artificial insemination with lesbian best friend Bea, who had a relationship with a lawyer, Rosa, for a while. Afterwards, she had a wild night with Ana, who became lesbian for her and became a stable couple. <br> {{Citation needed|reason=Per WP:VERIFY \u2013 Verify sexual orientation of all characters.|date=June 2018}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| 2003\u20132006 <br /> 2013\u2013 || ''[[Arrested Development (TV series)|Arrested Development]]'' || [[Fox Broad