ion came up. He was confirmed as bisexual by the actor. <br /> Dee, Charlie, and Frank have been described by the cast and creators as being at least bisexual. During a [[San Diego Comic-Con]] panel in 2013, when asked if Dennis was \"vaguely bisexual\", Glenn Howerton said \"Oh, I think all the characters are. I don't even know if it's 'vaguely'.\" Danny DeVito then went on to say \"The show is called \"All-ways Sunny In Philadelphia [...] We go all ways.\"<ref>{{Citation|author=Kristina Valencia|title=It's Always Sunny in Philadelphia panel at Comic Con 2013 Hall H!|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SJuWv6SU7C4|website=[[YouTube]]|date=July 25, 2013|accessdate=January 25, 2019}}</ref> The cast has mentioned multiple times on ''[[Conan (talk show)|Conan]]'' that all their characters are ambiguously gay.<ref>{{Citation|author=Lexi House|title=Glenn Howerton on Conan, 9/14/11|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nERjDLsgCgg|website=[[YouTube]]|date=February 11, 2018|accessdate=January 26, 2019}}</ref> They have gone on to say that they feel \"everyone\" might be gay, and that it is reflective of society, as they have never met anyone who isn't gay.<ref>{{Citation|title=The \"It's Always Sunny...\" Guys Are All A Little Gay|url=http://teamcoco.com/node/70672|website=[[Conan (talk show)|Conan]]|accessdate=26 January 2019|language=en}}</ref> <br /> Artemis is a friend of the gang and is likely bisexual. In a promotional video for the show she states that she has \"had lesbian encounters. ''Plural.'' [...] There were a couple years there, where scissoring some bull dyke was the only way I could get my squirts off.\" In the same promo she also asked if it \"cost extra to send this [dating] video to both sexes\".<ref>{{Citation|last=ALLNEWSUNNY|title=Phindin Love in Philly (It's Always Sunny in Philadelphia)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o-jumwebouU|website=[[YouTube]]|date=March 12, 2011|accessdate=January 25, 2019}}</ref> <br> {{Citation needed|reason=Per WP:VERIFY \u2013 Verify sexual orientation of all characters.|date=June 2018}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| 2005 || ''[[All About George]]'' || [[ITV Network|ITV]] <br />|| Russel || [[Rory Jennings]] || {{Citation needed|reason=Per WP:VERIFY \u2013 Verify sexual orientation of all characters.|date=June 2018}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| 2005 || {{hs|Comeback}}''[[The Comeback (TV series)|The Comeback]]'' || [[HBO]] || Mickey Deane || [[Robert Michael Morris]] || Mickey is a hairdresser and confidant to lead character Valerie Cherish ([[Lisa Kudrow]]) who, despite being obviously gay, believes he is closeted. {{Citation needed|reason=Per WP:VERIFY \u2013 Verify sexual orientation of all characters.|date=June 2018}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| 2005 || ''[[It's Me...Gerald]]'' || [[Showcase (Canadian TV channel)|Showcase]] || Gerald || [[Gerald L'Ecuyer]] || {{Citation needed|reason=Per WP:VERIFY \u2013 Verify sexual orientation of all characters.|date=June 2018}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| 2006\u20132013 || ''[[30 Rock]]'' || [[NBC]] || [[Devon Banks]] <br /> Jonathan <br /> J.D. Lutz <br /> Randy || [[Will Arnett]] <br /> [[Maulik Pancholy]]<br /> [[John Lutz]] <br /> Jeffery Self || Devon Banks is Jack Donaghy's nemesis, an executive who constantly tries to foil Jack's attempts to advance professionally. At first Devon is closeted but in the fifth season, it is revealed he has moved to Brooklyn and had children with an African-American dancer, Cashmere. Jonathan is Jack's assistant, who is smitten with his boss. J.D. Lutz is a TGS writer, whose sexual orientation was a mystery throughout the series. It was revealed in the series finale that he is bisexual. Randy is Liz Lemon's cousin. {{Citation needed|reason=Per WP:VERIFY \u2013 Verify sexual orientation of all characters.|date=June 2018}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| 2006\u20132007 || {{hs|Business}}''[[The Business (TV series)|The Business]]'' || [[Independent Film Channel|IFC]] || Terrence von Holtzen <br /> Wendell Cooper || Matt Silver <br /> Neil