air. {{Citation needed|reason=Per WP:VERIFY \u2013 Verify sexual orientation of all characters.|date=June 2018}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| 2008 || ''[[Sordid Lives: The Series]]'' || [[Logo (TV channel)|Logo]] || Earl \"Brother Boy\" Ingram <br /> Ty Williamson || [[Leslie Jordan]] <br /> [[Jason Dottley]] || Brother Boy likes to perform as [[Tammy Wynette]] and tries to escape from [[Conversion therapy|treatments to dehomosexualize him]].  Ty is an actor in Los Angeles coming to terms with his homosexuality. {{Citation needed|reason=Per WP:VERIFY \u2013 Verify sexual orientation of all characters.|date=June 2018}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| 2009\u20132015 || ''[[Nurse Jackie]]'' || [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]] || Mohammed \"Mo-Mo\" de la Cruz <br /> Thor Lundgren <br /> Dr. Eleanor O'Hara || [[Haaz Sleiman]] <br /> [[Stephen Wallem|Steve Wallem]] <br /> [[Eve Best]] || Mohammed and Thor are gay nurses at All Saints' Hospital. <br> Mohammed was dropped after the first season. The producers stated the reason being \"the character's storyline ran its course\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ausiellofiles.ew.com/2009/12/22/haaz-sleiman-leaves-nurse-jackie/|title=Exclusive: ''Nurse Jackie'' drops Mo-Mo!|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|date=December 22, 2009|publisher=EW.com|accessdate=December 27, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100114110136/http://ausiellofiles.ew.com/2009/12/22/haaz-sleiman-leaves-nurse-jackie/|archive-date=January 14, 2010|url-status=dead}}</ref> <br /> Eleanor is bisexual and in a relationship with a woman journalist in season 2.<ref>{{cite web |author=The Linster |title=\"Nurse Jackie\": The lesbian storyline cometh |url=https://www.afterellen.com/tv/70970-nurse-jackie-the-lesbian-storyline-cometh |website=[[AfterEllen]] |date=April 13, 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160424095552/https://www.afterellen.com/tv/70970-nurse-jackie-the-lesbian-storyline-cometh |archivedate=April 24, 2016}}</ref> {{Citation needed|reason=Per WP:VERIFY