to pressure from fans and both Morris and Rivera. The storyline saw great advances in the second season once the actresses were promoted to the main cast. They are seen making out on Brittany's bed in \"[[Duets (Glee)|Duets]]\" and also make reference to the lesbian sex act of [[scissoring]]. In \"[[Sexy (Glee)|Sexy]]\" Santana finally professes her love for Brittany and later admits that she is a lesbian. Brittany is thought to be bisexual or [[pansexual]]. <br /> Hiram and LeRoy Berry are Rachel's fathers. <br /> Unique is a transgender member of the rival Vocal Adrenaline show choir who identifies as female. She joins New Directions in season 4. <br> {{Citation needed|reason=Per WP:VERIFY \u2013 Verify sexual orientation of all characters.|date=June 2018}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|2009\u2013 || ''[[Modern Family]]'' || [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] || Mitchell Pritchett <br /> Cameron Tucker <br /> Haley Dunphy || [[Jesse Tyler Ferguson]] <br /> [[Eric Stonestreet]] <br /> [[Sarah Hyland]] || When the series begins, Mitchell and Cameron are gay men that have been together for five years and have an adopted Vietnamese-born daughter, Lilly. <br /> Haley is bisexual.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Logan |first1=Elizabeth |title=Sarah Hyland Says Her 'Modern Family' Character, Haley Dunphy, Is Bisexual |url=https://www.glamour.com/story/sarah-hyland-modern-family-character-bisexual |website=[[Glamour (magazine)|Glamour]] |date=November 2, 2017}}</ref> <br> {{Citation needed|reason=Per WP:VERIFY \u2013 Verify sexual orientation of all characters.|date=June 2018}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| 2009\u20132013 || ''[[Go Girls]]'' || [[TVNZ 2]] || Levi Hirsh<br />Kent || Leon Wadham<br />Josh McKenzie || Levi is a sassy gay Jewish man whose Go Girls pledge is to get revenge.<br />Levi's ex-boyfriend and first love since high school. {{Citation needed|reason=Per WP:VERIFY \u2013 Verify sexual orientation of all characters.|date=June 2018}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|} <!-- DO NOT REMOVE CLOS