.google.com/books?id=2pSH73isp94C&dq=isbn%3A0226872319&q=all+gay%2C+all+the+time#v=snippet&q=all%20gay%2C%20all%20the%20time&f=false Snippet]) (p. 100)</ref> Sal is lead character Hunter's ([[Stephen Dunham]]) boss.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Tropiano|first1=Stephen|title=The Prime Time Closet: A History of Gays and Lesbians on TV|date=2002|publisher=[[Applause Theatre & Cinema Books]]|isbn=978-1557835574 |url=https://archive.org/details/primetimecloseta00trop}} (p. 292)</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| 1999\u20132000 || ''[[Strangers with Candy]]'' || [[Comedy Central]] || Jerri Blank <br /> Geoffrey Jellineck <br /> Chuck Noblet || [[Amy Sedaris]] <br />[[Paul Dinello]] <br /> [[Stephen Colbert]] || Jerri is bisexual. Jellineck and Noblet carried on a clandestine affair. {{Citation needed|reason=Per WP:VERIFY \u2013 Verify sexual orientation of all characters.|date=June 2018}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| 1999\u20132001 || ''[[Beggars and Choosers (TV series)|Beggars and Choosers]]'' || [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]] || Malcolm Laffley || [[Tuc Watkins]] || Laffley is a television casting director who came out to disprove sexual harassment charges leveled at him by a woman. {{Citation needed|reason=Per WP:VERIFY \u2013 Verify sexual orientation of all characters.|date=June 2018}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|1999\u20132001 || ''[[Los Beltr\u00e1n]]'' || [[Telemundo]] || Fernando Salazar <br /> Kevin Lynch|| [[Gabriel Romero (actor)|Gabriel Romero]] <br /> [[James C. Leary]] || Fernando and Kevin are gay.  They are the first openly-gay characters on Spanish-language television, and first same-sex couple that marry. {{Citation needed|reason=Per WP:VERIFY \u2013 Verify sexual orientation of all characters.|date=June 2018}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|} <!-- DO NOT REMOVE CLOSING MARKUP CODE -->\n\n==2000s==\n<!--Using Visual Editor: please be very careful when using VE. VE is problematic with tables. See [[WP:VE]] > Limitations-->\n<!--[[WP:VERIFY]]: \"All material in Wikipedia mainspace, inclu