 1 finale, it is revealed that Eli and Tanner used to be police partners and had some sort of relationship during this time. This is part of the reason that they have since become enemies. <br> Joseph has stereotypical characteristics of a gay man and kisses Strauss in the finale, but this seems to be more out of fun than any real romantic interest in him. {{Citation needed|reason=Per WP:VERIFY \u2013 Verify sexual orientation of all characters.|date=June 2018}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|2019\u2013 || ''[[Dickinson (TV series)|Dickinson]]'' || [[Apple TV+]] || [[Emily Dickinson]] <br> Susan Gilbert || [[Hailee Steinfeld]] <br> [[Ella Hunt]] || Emily and Susan are in a secret homosexual relationship.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Estes|first1=Theo|title=Review: Emily Dickinson is America\u2019s Original Quirky Girl in \u201cDickinson\u201d|url=https://thespool.net/tv/2019/10/review-emily-dickinson-hailee-steinfeld/|website=The Spool|date=October 29, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Schuessler|first1=Jennifer|title=A Very Modern Emily Dickinson (Twerking Included)|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/10/30/arts/television/emily-dickinson-apple.html|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=October 30, 2019}}</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|2019\u2013 || ''[[Mrs. Fletcher]]'' || [[HBO]] || Margo || [[Jen Richards]] || Margo is a trans woman.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Haley |first1=Brendan |title=Mrs. Fletcher Is the Sex-Positive, Queer Show TV Needs Right Now |url=https://www.pride.com/tv/2019/10/30/mrs-fletcher-sex-positive-queer-show-tv-needs-right-now |website=Pride.com |publisher=[[Here Media]] |date=30 October 2019}}</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|2019\u2013 || ''[[High School Musical: The Musical: The Series]]'' || [[Disney+]] || Carol <br> Dana || [[Nicole Sullivan]] <br> Michelle Noh || Carol is _____. <br> Dana is _____. <br> Carol and Dana are Nini's mothers. {{Citation needed|reason=Per WP:VERIFY \u2013 Verify sexual orientation of all characters.|date=November 2019}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|2019\u