=\"top\"\n| 2020\u2013 || ''[[Avenue 5]]'' || [[HBO]] || Ryan Clark || [[Hugh Laurie]] || Clark has a husband and a wife, indicating he is bi or pansexual. {{Citation needed|reason=Per WP:VERIFY \u2013 Verify sexual orientation of all characters.|date=February 2020}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|2020\u2013 || ''[[Everything's Gonna Be Okay]]'' || [[Freeform (TV channel)|Freeform]] || Nicholas <br> Alex || [[Josh Thomas (comedian)|Josh Thomas]] <br> Adam Faison || Nicholas is gay.<ref>{{Cite magazine|last1=Berman|first1=Judy|title=In Party of Five and Everything's Gonna Be Okay, Freeform Reinvents the Orphan Saga for Gen Z|url=https://time.com/5758404/party-of-five-everythings-gonna-be-okay-review/|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=January 3, 2020|access-date=15 February 2020}}</ref> <br> Alex is gay and Nicholas' boyfriend.<ref>{{Cite web|last1=Harnick|first1=Chris|title=Under Josh Thomas' Watch, Everything's Gonna Be Okay|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/1112444/under-josh-thomas-watch-everything-s-gonna-be-okay|website=[[E! Online]]|date=January 16, 2020|accessdate=15 February 2020}}</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|2020\u2013 || ''[[Indebted]]'' || [[NBC]] || Joanna || [[Jessy Hodges]] || Joanna is lesbian.<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Reynolds|first1=Daniel|title=Fran Drescher Loves 'Hot Goss' and Her Lesbian Daughter in Indebted|url=https://www.advocate.com/television/2020/2/27/fran-drescher-loves-hot-goss-and-her-lesbian-daughter-indebted|work=[[The Advocate (LGBT magazine)|The Advocate]]|date=February 27, 2020}}</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|2020\u2013 || ''[[Feel Good (TV series)|Feel Good]]'' || [[Channel 4]] <br> [[Netflix]] || Mae <br> George || [[Mae Martin]] <br>  [[Charlotte Ritchie]] || Mae does not identify her sexual orientation. She has had relationships with men and women and is currently in a lesbian relationship. <br> George, Mae's girlfriend, identified as straight before she started dating Mae.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Feay|first1=Suzi|title=Feel Good brings comedy, love and other addictions to Channel 4|url=https://www.ft.com/content/d80b42aa-67a4-11ea-800d-da70cff6e4d3|work=[[Financial Times]]|date=March 17, 2020|url-access=limited|archiveurl=http://archive.is/vxxgh|archivedate=22 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Rutkowski|first1=Laura|title=Why Feel Good will give you a heart-on|url=https://www.virginmedia.com/virgin-tv-edit/tv/feel-good-channel-4-interviews|website=[[Virgin Media]]|date=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|2020\u2013 || ''[[High Fidelity (TV series)|High Fidelity]]'' || [[Hulu]] || Robyn \"Rob\" Brooks <br> Simon Miller <br> Blake ||  [[Zo\u00eb Kravitz]] <br> David H. Holmes <br> Edmund Donovan || Robyn is bisexual. She's trying to understand why her relationships are always doing something wrong. <br> Simon is gay and Robyn's ex-boyfriend. <br> Blake is gay. Simon and Blake are a couple. {{Citation needed|reason=Per WP:VERIFY \u2013 Verify sexual orientation of all characters.|date=March 2020}}\n|- valign=\"to\n|}<!-- DO NOT REMOVE CLOSING MARKUP CODE -->\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|LGBT|Television|Lists}}\n\n* [[List of LGBT characters in television and radio]]\n* [[List of comedy-drama television series]]\n* [[List of comedy television series]]\n* [[List of comedy and variety television programs with LGBT cast members]]\n* [[List of animated series with LGBT characters]]\n* [[List of dramatic television series with LGBT characters: 1970s\u20132000s]]\n* [[List of dramatic television series with LGBT characters: 2010s]]\n* [[List of dramatic television series with LGBT characters: 2020s]]\n* [[List of made-for-television films with LGBT characters]]\n* [[List of reality television programs with LGBT cast members]]\n* [[List of LGBT characters in soap operas]]\n* [[List of news and information television programs featuring LGBT subjects]]\n* [[List of television series with bisexual characters]]\n* [[List of fictional asexual characters]]\n* [[List of fictional non-binary characters]]\n* [[