{"title_page": "Cherie Mercado", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| image =\n| birth_name = Cherie Lei Mercado\n| birth_date = \n| occupation = [[Journalist]], [[Radio personality|Radio Commentator]]\n| yearsactive = 1994-2016, 2018-2019, 2020-present\n| spouse = Mike Santos<ref name=\"marketmonitor\">{{cite web |url=http://marketmonitor.com.ph/a-dream-fulfilled-an-escape-to-the-south-of-france/ |title=A dream fulfilled: An escape to the south of France (First part) |last=Mercado-Santos |first=Cherie  |date=12 January 2015 |website=The Market Monitor |publisher=Ana Publishing Incorporated |access-date=22 October 2015 |quote=She is the proud mother of two daughters, Christiana and Anabella, and happily shares life\u2019s journey and travel adventures with her stockbroker-husband Mike Santos.}}</ref>\n| children = Christiana Santos<ref>{{cite news |last=Pangilinan |first=Robbie |date=1 February 2010 |title=Teacher mommy |url=http://www.philstar.com/entertainment/545289/teacher-mommy |newspaper=[[The Philippine Star]] |location=Philippines |access-date=22 October 2015 }}</ref> <br/>Anabella Santos<ref name=\"marketmonitor\" />\n| website =\n}}\n\n'''Cherie Mercado-Santos''' is a Filipina broadcast journalist in the Philippines.\n\nCherie is married to Mike Santos, a stockbroker, and they have two children, Christiana and Anabella.<ref name=\"marketmonitor\" />\n\n==Career==\nWith 24 years of experience as a writer, reporter, producer, host and anchor, Cherie worked for the top three networks in the Philippines beginning her careers a news reporter and researcher at GMA Broadcasting Corp., then as one of the best live on-the-scene reporters for ABS-CBN News, before finally signing with TV5.\n\nPrior to joining TV5, she hosted ABS-CBN\u2019s Morning Show \u201cAlas Singko Y\u2019Medya\u201d, \u201cMagandang Umaga Bayan\u201d, The Global News and her own lifestyleshow on ANC, Coffee Talk with Cherie Mercado.\n\nAs a senior newscaster, she is a prominent figure in the news industry and well-respected for her poise, professionalism, great sense of style and hard-hitting news stories including her coverage of the Mindanao conflict.\n\nShe was chosen by Sky News Broadcasting in London to speak about the Philippines\u2019 coverage of the Royal Wedding.\n\nShe was the solo host and anchor for CNN Konek, a local franchise of CNN Connect the World hosted by CNN\u2019s senior anchor Becky Anderson. It airs on AksyonTV every weeknight at 7:30-8:00pm.\n\nShe was also co-hosts a radio program with news personality Paolo Bediones entitled \u201cTrabaho Lang with Paolo and Cherie\u201d, which airs every weeknight on Radyo5, 92.3 News FM from 8:00-9:30pm.\n\nShe was the co-anchor of late-night newscast entitled Aksyon JournalisMO together with Jove Francisco and Martin Andanar.\n\nShe was also the co-anchor of the late newscast entitled Pilipinas News, replaced Aksyon JournalisMO, together with Jove Francisco and Paolo Bediones.\n\nOn July 21, 2014, Mercado was moved to noontime newscast Aksyon sa Tanghali together with Raffy Tulfo.\n\nOn July 15, 2016, Mercado left TV5, her home network for 12 years to become the spokesperson of the [[Department of Transportation (Philippines)|Department of Transportation]] (DOTR).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rappler.com/business/211-governance/139967-cherie-mercado-new-dotc-spokesperson|title=TV5's Cherie Mercado is new transportation spokesperson|publisher=[[Rappler]]|last=dela Paz|first=Charisse|date=July 17, 2016|accessdate=July 17, 2016}}</ref> Mercado later resigned in May 2017 due to her motherhood.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.medianewser.com/2017/05/cherie-mercado-resigns-as-spokesperson.html|title=CHERIE MERCADO RESIGNS AS SPOKESPERSON OF THE DEPARTMENT OF TRANSPORTATION|publisher=Medianewser.com|date=May 19, 2017|accessdate=May 22, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn February 12, 2018, Mercado joined [[CNN Philippines]], as she takes over as a new anchor of the Evening Edition of [[CNN Philippines Newsroom|Newsroom]] replaced Mitzi Borromeo.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://twitter.com/cnnphilippines/status/963035084793106432|title=Join @cheriemercado now on Newsroom. (CNN Philippines on Twitter)|date=February 13, 2018|accessdate=February 13, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.medianewser.com/2018/01/cherie-mercado-joining-cnn-philippines.html|title=Former TV5 anchor Cherie Mercado joining CNN Philippines (Media Newser Philippines)|date=February 1, 2018|accessdate=February 1, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn September 3, 2018, Mercado moved to Mid-morning Filipino newscast ''Newsroom Ngayon''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.medianewser.com/2018/08/ruth-cabal-and-cherie-mercado-to-switch-roles.html|title=Ruth Cabal and Cherie Mercado to switch roles (Media Newser Philippines)|date=December 14, 2018|accessdate=December 14, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Position !! Network\n|-\n| 2020 || ''Kabalikat: Kasama si Cherie Mercado'' || Host || PBN\n|-\n| 2019 || ''CNN Philippines The Filipino Votes: Senatorial Forum'' || Co-Moderator || rowspan= 4 | [[CNN Philippines]]\n|-\n| 2018-2019 || ''[[Updates (CNN Philippines)|Updates]]'' || Various Contributor \n|-\n| 2018\u20132019 || ''[[CNN Philippines Newsroom|Newsroom Ngayon]]'' || News Anchor \n|-\n| 2018 || ''[[CNN Philippines Newsroom|Newsroom]]'' || News Anchor \n|-\n| 2014\u20132016 || ''[[Aksyon|Aksyon sa Tanghali]]'' || News Anchor || rowspan= 3 | [[5 (TV channel)|TV5]]\n|-\n| 2012\u20132014 || ''[[Pilipinas News]]'' || News Anchor \n|-\n| 2012 || ''[[Insider (television show)|Insider]]'' || Host\n|-\n| 2011\u20132013 || ''[[CNN Konek]]'' || News Anchor || [[AksyonTV]]\n|-\n| 2010\u20132012 || ''[[Aksyon JournalisMO]]'' || News Anchor || rowspan= 4 | [[5 (TV channel)|TV5]]\n|-\n| 2010\u20132011 || ''[[Sapul sa Singko]]'' || Host\n|-\n| 2010 || ''[[Aksyon|Aksyon Weekend]]'' || News Anchor \n|-\n| 2008\u20132010 || || News Anchor \n|-\n| 2004\u20132008 || ''[[Big News]]'' || News Anchor || [[5 (TV channel)|ABC]]\n|-\n| 2001-2002 || ''Coffee Talk with Cherie Mercado'' || Host || [[ABS-CBN News Channel|ANC]] \n|-\n| 2001-2004 || ''[[Magandang Umaga, Pilipinas|Alas Singko y Medya]]'' || Host || rowspan= 4 | [[ABS-CBN (TV network)|ABS-CBN]]\n|-\n| 1998\u20132001 || ''[[Global News (ABS-CBN)|Global News]]'' || News Anchor \n|-\n| 1996\u20132001 || ''[[Balitang K]]'' || Reporter\n|-\n| 1995\u20132004 || ''[[The Weekend News (ABS-CBN)|The Weekend News]]'' || News Anchor \n|}\n\n===Radio===\n* Trabaho Lang! (2013\u20132014; 2015\u20132016) - [[DWFM|Radyo5 92.3 News FM]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mercado, Cherie}}\n[[Category:CNN people]]\n[[Category:ABS-CBN News and Current Affairs people]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Filipino television news anchors]]\n[[Category:Filipino radio journalists]]\n[[Category:People from Bulacan]]\n[[Category:News5 people]]\n[[Category:Duterte Administration personnel]]\n[[Category:Filipino women journalists]]\n[[Category:Women radio journalists]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| image =\n| birth_name = Cherie Lei Mercado\n| birth_date = \n| occupation = [[Journalist]], [[Radio personality|Radio Commentator]]\n| yearsactive = 1994-2016, 2018-2019, 2020-present\n| spouse = Mike Santos<ref name=\"marketmonitor\">{{cite web |url=http://marketmonitor.com.ph/a-dream-fulfilled-an-escape-to-the-south-of-france/ |title=A dream fulfilled: An escape to the south of France (First part) |last=Mercado-Santos |first=Cherie  |date=12 January 2015 |website=The Market Monitor |publisher=Ana Publishing Incorporated |access-date=22 October 2015 |quote=She is the proud mother of two daughters, Christiana and Anabella, and happily shares life\u2019s journey and travel adventures with her stockbroker-husband Mike Santos.}}</ref>\n| children = Christiana Santos<ref>{{cite news |last=Pangilinan |first=Robbie |date=1 February 2010 |title=Teacher mommy |url=http://www.philstar.com/entertainment/545289/teacher-mommy |newspaper=[[The Philippine Star]] |location=Philippines |access-date=22 October 2015 }}</ref> <br/>Anabella Santos<ref name=\"marketmonitor\" />\n| website =\n}}\n\n'''Cherie Mercado-Santos''' is a Filipina broadcast journalist in the Philippines.\n\nCherie is married to Mike Santos, a stockbroker, and they have two children, Christiana and Anabella.<ref name=\"marketmonitor\" />\n\n==Career==\nWith 24 years of experience as a writer, reporter, producer, host and anchor, Cherie worked for the top three networks in the Philippines beginning her careers a news reporter and researcher at GMA Broadcasting Corp., then as one of the best live on-the-scene reporters for ABS-CBN News, before finally signing with TV5.\n\nPrior to joining TV5, she hosted ABS-CBN\u2019s Morning Show \u201cAlas Singko Y\u2019Medya\u201d, \u201cMagandang Umaga Bayan\u201d, The Global News and her own lifestyleshow on ANC, Coffee Talk with Cherie Mercado.\n\nAs a senior newscaster, she is a prominent figure in the news industry and well-respected for her poise, professionalism, great sense of style and hard-hitting news stories including her coverage of the Mindanao conflict.\n\nShe was chosen by Sky News Broadcasting in London to speak about the Philippines\u2019 coverage of the Royal Wedding.\n\nShe was the solo host and anchor for CNN Konek, a local franchise of CNN Connect the World hosted by CNN\u2019s senior anchor Becky Anderson. It airs on AksyonTV every weeknight at 7:30-8:00pm.\n\nShe was also co-hosts a radio program with news personality Paolo Bediones entitled \u201cTrabaho Lang with Paolo and Cherie\u201d, which airs every weeknight on Radyo5, 92.3 News FM from 8:00-9:30pm.\n\nShe was the co-anchor of late-night newscast entitled Aksyon JournalisMO together with Jove Francisco and Martin Andanar.\n\nShe was also the co-anchor of the late newscast entitled Pilipinas News, replaced Aksyon JournalisMO, together with Jove Francisco and Paolo Bediones.\n\nOn July 21, 2014, Mercado was moved to noontime newscast Aksyon sa Tanghali together with Raffy Tulfo.\n\nOn July 15, 2016, Mercado left TV5, her home network for 12 years to become the spokesperson of the [[Department of Transportation (Philippines)|Department of Transportation]] (DOTR).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rappler.com/business/211-governance/139967-cherie-mercado-new-dotc-spokesperson|title=TV5's Cherie Mercado is new transportation spokesperson|publisher=[[Rappler]]|last=dela Paz|first=Charisse|date=July 17, 2016|accessdate=July 17, 2016}}</ref> Mercado later resigned in May 2017 due to her motherhood.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.medianewser.com/2017/05/cherie-mercado-resigns-as-spokesperson.html|title=CHERIE MERCADO RESIGNS AS SPOKESPERSON OF THE DEPARTMENT OF TRANSPORTATION|publisher=Medianewser.com|date=May 19, 2017|accessdate=May 22, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn February 12, 2018, Mercado joined [[CNN Philippines]], as she takes over as a new anchor of the Evening Edition of [[CNN Philippines Newsroom|Newsroom]] replaced Mitzi Borromeo.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://twitter.com/cnnphilippines/status/963035084793106432|title=Join @cheriemercado now on Newsroom. (CNN Philippines on Twitter)|date=February 13, 2018|accessdate=February 13, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.medianewser.com/2018/01/cherie-mercado-joining-cnn-philippines.html|title=Former TV5 anchor Cherie Mercado joining CNN Philippines (Media Newser Philippines)|date=February 1, 2018|accessdate=February 1, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn September 3, 2018, Mercado moved to Mid-morning Filipino newscast ''Newsroom Ngayon''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.medianewser.com/2018/08/ruth-cabal-and-cherie-mercado-to-switch-roles.html|title=Ruth Cabal and Cherie Mercado to switch roles (Media Newser Philippines)|date=December 14, 2018|accessdate=December 14, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Television===\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"ma